id: An id to refer to each dataset or model by
parent: The parent of the derivative dataset
name: The name of the dataset.
dataset or model?: "dataset" if dataset and "model" if pre-trained model class (Oftentimes, multiple implementations of the same model class exist, possibly through multiple repositories)
assoc. paper sampled: "1" if we used the associated paper of the dataset to generate our corpus
num. sampled: The number of papers in our corpus citing the associated paper.
doc. uses: The number of papers in our corpus where we could confirm the use of the dataset.
The number of documented uses of a dataset that cite the associated paper.
2020 doc. uses: The number of papers published in 2020 that we documented. Numbers are included for DukeMTMC and MS-Celeb-1M, which were both taken down in June 2019. LFW has not been retracted.
new application: "1" if the derivative explicitly or implicitly enables a task that can raise ethical questions.
attribute annotations: "1" if the derivative introduces sensitive attribute annotations.
post-processing: "1" if the derivative post-processes the original images, i.e., by aligning, cropping, or cleaning.
still available: "1" if we could confirm that the dataset / pre-trained model is still accessible
"1" if the derivative includes the original images in some form.
license type: The license under which the dataset or model is released. If available in multiple locations, we list all unique license types.
prohibits comm. use: "prohibits" if the available license clearly prohibits commercial use. "some" if some available licenses clearly prohibit commercial use.
access url: The site where a dataset can be accessed. In some cases, when the datset is no longer available, we were able to find an archived version of such a site.
